ğŸ“¦ Usage
./backupbuddy.sh -s <source> -d <destination> [-v] [-h]

---

## ğŸ”§ Options

Option	Description
-s	Path to the source file or directory (required)
-d	Path to the destination directory (required)
-v	Show version info (optional)
-h	Show help message

---

## ğŸ“Œ Example
./backupbuddy.sh -s ~/Documents/report.pdf -d ~/Backups
This will create a compressed backup of report.pdf in the ~/Backups directory.

